The possibility of individual counting of the ballots in this year's elections in Michoacán a reality, according to the Programa de Resultados Electorales Preliminares (PREP) issued data is the difference between the first and second place in the gubernatorial elections less than 27 percent, counted 879 votes out of a total of 6074 has not yet been counted.
In this sense, the President of the Consejo General del Instituto Electoral de Michoacán (IEM), María de los Ángeles Llanderal Zaragoza, recalled that just last 9 November the election rather than a set of rules for the harmonisation of local rules with the reform of the federal states had adopted in Electoral matters.
It should be remembered that Michoacán neither his political constitution nor election law nor its law on the election of justice had adapted to the reforms adopted by Congress, so this round were not in force in this election. The governor Leonel Godoy Rangel avoided their publication in the State Gazette within the allotted time with the argument to have any objections.
On 9 November, the Supreme Court of Mexico (SCJN) on the constitutional complaint filed by the local legislature and the voice of the State Ombudsman to the constitutional reforms as "invalid and illegal" because this does not have the right to "decide or impose a veto against it."
María de los Ángeles Llanderal said in an interview on the possibility of individual counting of the votes that, thanks to the adoption of the directives by the Consejo General del IEM now the possibility that auszählen local election authority, the ballot papers in part or in full.
It can be counted under the following conditions in one or more electoral votes packages contained some of the results in the protocols do not agree; the Protocol on the count and berechnung is not aktenmäßig, or it is not in possession of the chairman of the electoral commission or there are obvious errors or amendments in the protocols.
In addition, the total count of the full pressure of ballot papers, if there is a difference between the presumed winner and, in the second place, which is equal to or less than one percent, provided at the beginning of the session is an explicit request of the party or coalition chairman, who is the second of the candidates.
The count can be done in their entirety if, after the conclusion of the proper calculation that is the difference between the presumed winner and the candidates in the second place equal to or less than one percent, provided that it is an explicit request by a representative of the party, whose candidate second, above, in which case the ballot packages that have been exposed to a partial count.
It is worth noting that the elections in Morelia in the same situation where, under PREP the difference between the first and second place barely 0.16 percent, even though the votes of 129 out of a total of 923 electoral protocols have not yet been counted.
